👋🏻Hello old friends <+> long time. Hope all is well in your world. first post on this page in a few weeks shy of a year. So much has happened, I dont even know where to begin. Its tempting to not even try to fill in the gaps... Thinkin I'll just post up something glorious and pretend I never missed a beat. See how long I can keep the streak goin for. 🤣 
:::
::
:
📸 ❤️ I was fortunate enough to be asked to tell wedding day stories for well over a dozen couples this year. Things have evolved and many of those stories were done hybrid [photo+video] 🎥 
::
I’ve got a lot of exciting stuff to fill this place with. 
::
Kickin thing off with Lauren + Jesse, soaking up golden hour on the lake. Video highlight from this day is soon to follow

HEY YOU! Stop 🛑 your scroll, at least vertically… :) take it horizontally through this sequence, it’s worth it 😂 … 
::
:
standing at the front of the aisle. Guests are seated… live music has just started and everyone is getting ready to walk down the aisle…  AND THEN SUDDENLY THE SPRINKLERS pop up and COME ON 😜  #%&$ !?! people shriek as they scramble into organized chaos, much like the November Rain video. the musicians throw their instruments over their head in attempt to keep it dry.. Within a matter of seconds the seats are wet. Everyones wet. There’s nowhere to go.. and I can’t help do anything but laugh and shoot away and document the moment and the absurdity of it all. I like to think that the night before was some disgruntled workers last day, in order to get one final jam he switched the sprinklers to ceremony start time 🤪 cause otherwise there’s no acceptable explanation 
:::
::
:
Rather than post another polished portfolio piece today, I opted for the real life stuff that weddings are made of. I get paid the big bucks to stand there and land moments like these😎 and in 13  years of shooting I’ve seen so many. Soooo, more to come <+> 
:::
:: 
Oh and if you’re still here reading this, how about that last guy walking through the water, no f**ks given. I was tempted to photoshop the meme “thug life” glasses and joint onto him … cause let’s me honest, dude was unphased and it was badass. 😎 this wedding took place many years ago so I can’t recall who he was, so I like to pretend he’s the father of the bride bout ready to kick some ass 😆
:::
::
:

Dusting the cobwebs off over here. 📸❤️Been shooting a bunch but you wouldn’t know it by the way I’ve shunned IG and FB.  Probably looks like I’ve been hibernating 😴 
::::
:: Then this week I have a couple leads roll in [plus another in the requests folder from months back] and it makes me think 🤔 it might be worth putting some time in to spruce the place up 😂 Soooo here it goes. Kicking things off with these images…. Scroll to see variants. What do you think?? 🙃
.:.:.:.
I know.. a far leap from what I usually post but I think I’m going to start doing a preplanned artistic edit for every wedding, elopement, proposal, engagement creative type shoot I do in the future. It was challenging + fun… besides, I’ve been doing this so long now that it feels good to jump outside my comfort zone. 
:::

Rocking the cam professionally for over a decade now and I can honestly say that I still enjoy weddings 📸❤️ It’s not for everyone, that’s for sure… but I LOVE em. I feed off the energy ⚡️and thrive in the moment. Keeps me on my toes. I know there are going to be a ton of amazing moments coming at me all day/night… at this stage I know when and where these generally present themselves but must still stay attentive to and anticipate them in order to land em. The difference between a fraction of a second can be the difference between the most epic shot 🙌🏻. OR a blink/ strange expression.. = throw away. 🚫

Weddings are a celebration that test the skills of a photographer💪🏼They move quick. There’s no repeats. Its crucial to stay in tune with the moments coming at you while being creative and displaying abilities in damn near every genre of photography:  Candid / photojournalism, portraiture, still life- flowers/food etc, architecture, macro, fashion, creative- fine art/ conceptual… you name it, kicking ass behind the lens all day will test each area and that’s what keeps it fresh. 
:::

@rikkievelyn & @the_crankyj 💯 thank you for a wonderful adventure back to Cali. 🌅 Sunrise maternity session at #lookingglassfalls 📸❤️ I’m typically more of a late nighter but in order to beat crowds, have the waterfall all to ourselves, get the best shots possible… we set alarms for before sunrise and made the drive up!!
:::
::
:
You ever done a sunrise shoot at a waterfall before!?! Me neither.. 🙃 It’s freakin cold! 🥶 my hands started goin numb quickly, luckily I had gloves … I can only imagine how they felt out there at the base of the falls. ❄️ These two are absolutely tough as nails and dedicated to the vision they sent me. That icy mist blasting off the rocky water at the bottom of the falls was bone chilling. 
:::
::
:

I’d never been to looking glass before and was told it was tricky to shoot and the sun rises up behind the falls. Thankfully it was overcast and the clouds acted as a softbox diffusing the backlight to a nice even glow… here’s a handful of glory for the feed on this rainy afternoon 🌧️
:::

As you may or may not know @nofx is callin it quits. It was a good run… wasn’t it!? My gawwwd WTTH&B was such a great album. Soundtrack of my youth. I had the pleasure of seeing them a dozen times over the years between warped tours, the @theglasshousepomona , @hobanaheim  etc. I didn’t realize how spoiled I was growing up in SoCal with all the good shows happening around me constantly. Till I moved out to the woods and realized nobody really comes to NC 🙃 sad day. 
:::
::
:
Along with attending shows I’ve had the opportunity to photograph em twice. 📸🔥 This image has been selected to be made into a skateboard and up for resale at the punk rock museum in Las Vegas that Mike opened up🤘🏻 scroll to see a couple prototypes I’ve recently had sent to me 🔥 the run will be limited to 150, I’m excited these look good on old school/ pool shapes. More images to come including a killer shot of Melvin that will likely be in a future run of decks 🛹

Been sorting through images taken in 2023 sprucing up the existing wedding blog and building a new website for 2024. I was deleting old weddings from 2011 -2012 from the blog last night, trying to lighten the load of the website as I fill it up with the new. Getting all nostalgic with a flood of memories from the old days. So many beautiful portraits of lovely people… fills my heart with gratitude. It’s been a crazy ride. Definitely come a long way in 15 years of shooting. Growing together with couples through the years, from 📷❤️ proposal to wedding… maternity and later family photos over the years is the greatest. Some of you I’ve known for damn near 15 years and I cherish that ❤️ I will miss my Cali brides, grooms and families as the new chapter is beginning in NC
